text.__SUMMARY__:
Grevillea reptans, also known as the Tin Can Bay grevillea, is a shrub of the genus Grevillea native to south east Queensland.
The prostrate shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 metres (1.0 ft) and has long branches with non-glaucous angular ridges branchlets. It has simple linear leaves with a blade that is 6 to 12 millimetres (0.24 to 0.47 in) long and 1 to 2 mm (0.04 to 0.08 in) wide.
